{"key":"post-17867655","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>17867655</id>\n<content>Don't dunk a monotub until at least after first flush if even then.&amp;nbsp; They often break.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Simply pour a glass or two of water over it to rehydrate the substrate as needed.&amp;nbsp; I've never bought into 'set and forget'.&amp;nbsp; You can also pour water around the edges if they've pulled away from the sides.&amp;nbsp; Just put as much water as can be totally absorbed in a few hours.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>17873131</next>\n<prev>17866886</prev>\n<first>17866862</first>\n<last>17873131</last>\n<when>1361884222</when>\n<utime>02/26/13 03:10 PM</utime>\n</post>"}